{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":560,"text":"I'm going to speak to you\nabout the global refugee crisis"},{"time":4360,"text":"and my aim is to show you that this crisis"},{"time":8200,"text":"is manageable, not unsolvable,"},{"time":11960,"text":"but also show you that this is\nas much about us and who we are"},{"time":17280,"text":"as it is a trial of the refugees\non the front line."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21320,"text":"For me, this is not\njust a professional obligation,"},{"time":24160,"text":"because I run an NGO supporting refugees\nand displaced people around the world."},{"time":29120,"text":"It's personal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31320,"text":"I love this picture."},{"time":33920,"text":"That really handsome guy on the right,"},{"time":36040,"text":"that's not me."},{"time":37760,"text":"That's my dad, Ralph, in London, in 1940"},{"time":41360,"text":"with his father Samuel."},{"time":43920,"text":"They were Jewish refugees from Belgium."},{"time":46440,"text":"They fled the day the Nazis invaded."},{"time":50600,"text":"And I love this picture, too."},{"time":52640,"text":"It's a group of refugee children"},{"time":55480,"text":"arriving in England in 1946 from Poland."},{"time":59000,"text":"And in the middle is my mother, Marion."},{"time":62640,"text":"She was sent to start a new life"},{"time":65680,"text":"in a new country"},{"time":67200,"text":"on her own"},{"time":68480,"text":"at the age of 12."},{"time":70920,"text":"I know this:"},{"time":72560,"text":"if Britain had not admitted refugees"},{"time":75840,"text":"in the 1940s,"},{"time":77800,"text":"I certainly would not be here today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82240,"text":"Yet 70 years on,\nthe wheel has come full circle."},{"time":86840,"text":"The sound is of walls being built,"},{"time":89880,"text":"vengeful political rhetoric,"},{"time":92400,"text":"humanitarian values and principles on fire"},{"time":96760,"text":"in the very countries\nthat 70 years ago said never again"},{"time":100680,"text":"to statelessness and hopelessness\nfor the victims of war."},{"time":106600,"text":"Last year, every minute,"},{"time":110320,"text":"24 more people were displaced\nfrom their homes"},{"time":113680,"text":"by conflict, violence and persecution:"},{"time":117160,"text":"another chemical weapon attack in Syria,"},{"time":119880,"text":"the Taliban on the rampage in Afghanistan,"},{"time":123360,"text":"girls driven from their school\nin northeast Nigeria by Boko Haram."},{"time":129800,"text":"These are not people\nmoving to another country"},{"time":133320,"text":"to get a better life."},{"time":135280,"text":"They're fleeing for their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139080,"text":"It's a real tragedy"},{"time":141520,"text":"that the world's most famous refugee\ncan't come to speak to you here today."},{"time":147240,"text":"Many of you will know this picture."},{"time":149800,"text":"It shows the lifeless body"},{"time":152440,"text":"of five-year-old Alan Kurdi,"},{"time":154560,"text":"a Syrian refugee who died\nin the Mediterranean in 2015."},{"time":159040,"text":"He died alongside 3,700 others\ntrying to get to Europe."},{"time":164440,"text":"The next year, 2016,"},{"time":166720,"text":"5,000 people died."},{"time":170840,"text":"It's too late for them,"},{"time":173240,"text":"but it's not too late\nfor millions of others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"It's not too late\nfor people like Frederick."},{"time":178640,"text":"I met him in the Nyarugusu\nrefugee camp in Tanzania."},{"time":182160,"text":"He's from Burundi."},{"time":183720,"text":"He wanted to know\nwhere could he complete his studies."},{"time":186320,"text":"He'd done 11 years of schooling.\nHe wanted a 12th year."},{"time":189440,"text":"He said to me, \"I pray\nthat my days do not end here"},{"time":194080,"text":"in this refugee camp.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":196200,"text":"And it's not too late for Halud."},{"time":199480,"text":"Her parents were Palestinian refugees"},{"time":202200,"text":"living in the Yarmouk refugee camp\noutside Damascus."},{"time":205480,"text":"She was born to refugee parents,"},{"time":207040,"text":"and now she's a refugee\nherself in Lebanon."},{"time":210520,"text":"She's working for the International\nRescue Committee to help other refugees,"},{"time":214840,"text":"but she has no certainty at all"},{"time":217840,"text":"about her future,"},{"time":220000,"text":"where it is or what it holds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222400,"text":"This talk is about Frederick, about Halud"},{"time":226320,"text":"and about millions like them:"},{"time":228320,"text":"why they're displaced,"},{"time":230280,"text":"how they survive, what help they need\nand what our responsibilities are."},{"time":235600,"text":"I truly believe this,"},{"time":238440,"text":"that the biggest question\nin the 21st century"},{"time":241760,"text":"concerns our duty to strangers."},{"time":245320,"text":"The future \"you\" is about your duties"},{"time":248600,"text":"to strangers."},{"time":250440,"text":"You know better than anyone,"},{"time":251840,"text":"the world is more connected\nthan ever before,"},{"time":256519,"text":"yet the great danger"},{"time":258440,"text":"is that we're consumed by our divisions."},{"time":262000,"text":"And there is no better test of that"},{"time":264280,"text":"than how we treat refugees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266840,"text":"Here are the facts: 65 million people"},{"time":269800,"text":"displaced from their homes\nby violence and persecution last year."},{"time":273040,"text":"If it was a country,"},{"time":274800,"text":"that would be the 21st\nlargest country in the world."},{"time":278880,"text":"Most of those people, about 40 million,\nstay within their own home country,"},{"time":283800,"text":"but 25 million are refugees."},{"time":285400,"text":"That means they cross a border\ninto a neighboring state."},{"time":289120,"text":"Most of them are living in poor countries,"},{"time":293160,"text":"relatively poor or lower-middle-income\ncountries, like Lebanon,"},{"time":296200,"text":"where Halud is living."},{"time":298880,"text":"In Lebanon, one\nin four people is a refugee,"},{"time":303560,"text":"a quarter of the whole population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306840,"text":"And refugees stay for a long time."},{"time":308960,"text":"The average length of displacement"},{"time":311080,"text":"is 10 years."},{"time":313320,"text":"I went to what was the world's\nlargest refugee camp, in eastern Kenya."},{"time":318080,"text":"It's called Dadaab."},{"time":319320,"text":"It was built in 1991-92"},{"time":321480,"text":"as a \"temporary camp\"\nfor Somalis fleeing the civil war."},{"time":325920,"text":"I met Silo."},{"time":327720,"text":"And na√Øvely I said to Silo,"},{"time":330560,"text":"\"Do you think you'll ever\ngo home to Somalia?\""},{"time":333880,"text":"And she said, \"What do you mean, go home?"},{"time":336320,"text":"I was born here.\""},{"time":338720,"text":"And then when I asked the camp management"},{"time":340840,"text":"how many of the 330,000 people\nin that camp were born there,"},{"time":344920,"text":"they gave me the answer:"},{"time":347160,"text":"100,000."},{"time":349840,"text":"That's what long-term displacement means."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353440,"text":"Now, the causes of this are deep:"},{"time":355920,"text":"weak states that can't\nsupport their own people,"},{"time":358840,"text":"an international political system"},{"time":361280,"text":"weaker than at any time since 1945"},{"time":364320,"text":"and differences over theology, governance,\nengagement with the outside world"},{"time":368440,"text":"in significant parts of the Muslim world."},{"time":372680,"text":"Now, those are long-term,\ngenerational challenges."},{"time":375880,"text":"That's why I say that this refugee crisis\nis a trend and not a blip."},{"time":380360,"text":"And it's complex, and when you have\nbig, large, long-term, complex problems,"},{"time":384920,"text":"people think nothing can be done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388120,"text":"When Pope Francis went to Lampedusa,"},{"time":391360,"text":"off the coast of Italy, in 2014,"},{"time":392960,"text":"he accused all of us\nand the global population"},{"time":396280,"text":"of what he called\n\"the globalization of indifference.\""},{"time":400760,"text":"It's a haunting phrase."},{"time":402000,"text":"It means that our hearts\nhave turned to stone."},{"time":406560,"text":"Now, I don't know, you tell me."},{"time":408400,"text":"Are you allowed to argue with the Pope,\neven at a TED conference?"},{"time":412880,"text":"But I think it's not right."},{"time":414320,"text":"I think people do want\nto make a difference,"},{"time":416440,"text":"but they just don't know whether\nthere are any solutions to this crisis."},{"time":420160,"text":"And what I want to tell you today"},{"time":422000,"text":"is that though the problems are real,\nthe solutions are real, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425800,"text":"Solution one:"},{"time":427160,"text":"these refugees need to get into work\nin the countries where they're living,"},{"time":430760,"text":"and the countries where they're living\nneed massive economic support."},{"time":434040,"text":"In Uganda in 2014, they did a study:"},{"time":436680,"text":"80 percent of refugees\nin the capital city Kampala"},{"time":439600,"text":"needed no humanitarian aid\nbecause they were working."},{"time":442360,"text":"They were supported into work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444400,"text":"Solution number two:"},{"time":446200,"text":"education for kids\nis a lifeline, not a luxury,"},{"time":450280,"text":"when you're displaced for so long."},{"time":453480,"text":"Kids can bounce back when they're given\nthe proper social, emotional support"},{"time":457600,"text":"alongside literacy and numeracy."},{"time":459360,"text":"I've seen it for myself."},{"time":462680,"text":"But half of the world's refugee children\nof primary school age"},{"time":466040,"text":"get no education at all,"},{"time":468040,"text":"and three-quarters of secondary school age\nget no education at all."},{"time":471440,"text":"That's crazy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473760,"text":"Solution number three:"},{"time":476280,"text":"most refugees are in urban areas,\nin cities, not in camps."},{"time":479760,"text":"What would you or I want\nif we were a refugee in a city?"},{"time":482440,"text":"We would want money\nto pay rent or buy clothes."},{"time":486600,"text":"That is the future\nof the humanitarian system,"},{"time":488800,"text":"or a significant part of it:"},{"time":490200,"text":"give people cash so that\nyou boost the power of refugees"},{"time":492880,"text":"and you'll help the local economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494880,"text":"And there's a fourth solution, too,"},{"time":496880,"text":"that's controversial\nbut needs to be talked about."},{"time":499640,"text":"The most vulnerable refugees\nneed to be given a new start"},{"time":503160,"text":"and a new life in a new country,"},{"time":506120,"text":"including in the West."},{"time":508080,"text":"The numbers are relatively small,\nhundreds of thousands, not millions,"},{"time":512320,"text":"but the symbolism is huge."},{"time":515880,"text":"Now is not the time\nto be banning refugees,"},{"time":518600,"text":"as the Trump administration proposes."},{"time":520440,"text":"It's a time to be embracing people\nwho are victims of terror."},{"time":524159,"text":"And remember --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":525400,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532480,"text":"Remember, anyone who asks you,\n\"Are they properly vetted?\""},{"time":536240,"text":"that's a really sensible\nand good question to ask."},{"time":540280,"text":"The truth is, refugees\narriving for resettlement"},{"time":544440,"text":"are more vetted than any other population\narriving in our countries."},{"time":548120,"text":"So while it's reasonable\nto ask the question,"},{"time":550280,"text":"it's not reasonable to say that refugee\nis another word for terrorist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555120,"text":"Now, what happens --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":556360,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":559760,"text":"What happens when refugees can't get work,"},{"time":562920,"text":"they can't get their kids into school,"},{"time":564800,"text":"they can't get cash,\nthey can't get a legal route to hope?"},{"time":567880,"text":"What happens is they take risky journeys."},{"time":570440,"text":"I went to Lesbos, this beautiful\nGreek island, two years ago."},{"time":575200,"text":"It's a home to 90,000 people."},{"time":577080,"text":"In one year, 500,000 refugees\nwent across the island."},{"time":581240,"text":"And I want to show you what I saw"},{"time":583080,"text":"when I drove across\nto the north of the island:"},{"time":586440,"text":"a pile of life jackets\nof those who had made it to shore."},{"time":590840,"text":"And when I looked closer,"},{"time":592440,"text":"there were small\nlife jackets for children,"},{"time":594920,"text":"yellow ones."},{"time":596320,"text":"And I took this picture."},{"time":598480,"text":"You probably can't see the writing,\nbut I want to read it for you."},{"time":601640,"text":"\"Warning: will not\nprotect against drowning.\""},{"time":605920,"text":"So in the 21st century,"},{"time":608440,"text":"children are being given life jackets"},{"time":610720,"text":"to reach safety in Europe"},{"time":612880,"text":"even though those jackets\nwill not save their lives"},{"time":616240,"text":"if they fall out of the boat\nthat is taking them there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620800,"text":"This is not just a crisis, it's a test."},{"time":625760,"text":"It's a test that civilizations\nhave faced down the ages."},{"time":629560,"text":"It's a test of our humanity."},{"time":632000,"text":"It's a test of us in the Western world"},{"time":634320,"text":"of who we are and what we stand for."},{"time":639160,"text":"It's a test of our character,\nnot just our policies."},{"time":642960,"text":"And refugees are a hard case."},{"time":645160,"text":"They do come from faraway\nparts of the world."},{"time":648160,"text":"They have been through trauma."},{"time":650080,"text":"They're often of a different religion."},{"time":652200,"text":"Those are precisely the reasons\nwe should be helping refugees,"},{"time":655400,"text":"not a reason not to help them."},{"time":657400,"text":"And it's a reason to help them\nbecause of what it says about us."},{"time":662480,"text":"It's revealing of our values."},{"time":665120,"text":"Empathy and altruism are two\nof the foundations of civilization."},{"time":671320,"text":"Turn that empathy and altruism into action"},{"time":673760,"text":"and we live out a basic moral credo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676960,"text":"And in the modern world,\nwe have no excuse."},{"time":679240,"text":"We can't say we don't know\nwhat's happening in Juba, South Sudan,"},{"time":683360,"text":"or Aleppo, Syria."},{"time":684960,"text":"It's there, in our smartphone"},{"time":687880,"text":"in our hand."},{"time":689280,"text":"Ignorance is no excuse at all."},{"time":691880,"text":"Fail to help, and we show\nwe have no moral compass at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697080,"text":"It's also revealing about\nwhether we know our own history."},{"time":700960,"text":"The reason that refugees\nhave rights around the world"},{"time":703480,"text":"is because of extraordinary\nWestern leadership"},{"time":706280,"text":"by statesmen and women\nafter the Second World War"},{"time":708640,"text":"that became universal rights."},{"time":711640,"text":"Trash the protections of refugees,\nand we trash our own history."},{"time":716400,"text":"This is --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":717640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":719360,"text":"This is also revealing\nabout the power of democracy"},{"time":723400,"text":"as a refuge from dictatorship."},{"time":725680,"text":"How many politicians have you heard say,"},{"time":728760,"text":"\"We believe in the power of our example,\nnot the example of our power.\""},{"time":733600,"text":"What they mean is what we stand for\nis more important than the bombs we drop."},{"time":738360,"text":"Refugees seeking sanctuary"},{"time":740800,"text":"have seen the West as a source\nof hope and a place of haven."},{"time":746720,"text":"Russians, Iranians,"},{"time":749480,"text":"Chinese, Eritreans, Cubans,"},{"time":751800,"text":"they've come to the West for safety."},{"time":755480,"text":"We throw that away at our peril."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758120,"text":"And there's one other thing\nit reveals about us:"},{"time":760400,"text":"whether we have any humility\nfor our own mistakes."},{"time":763320,"text":"I'm not one of these people"},{"time":765200,"text":"who believes that all the problems\nin the world are caused by the West."},{"time":768560,"text":"They're not."},{"time":769800,"text":"But when we make mistakes,\nwe should recognize it."},{"time":772880,"text":"It's not an accident\nthat the country which has taken"},{"time":775400,"text":"more refugees than any other,\nthe United States,"},{"time":777680,"text":"has taken more refugees from Vietnam\nthan any other country."},{"time":781960,"text":"It speaks to the history."},{"time":784200,"text":"But there's more recent history,\nin Iraq and Afghanistan."},{"time":787560,"text":"You can't make up\nfor foreign policy errors"},{"time":791320,"text":"by humanitarian action,"},{"time":792920,"text":"but when you break something,\nyou have a duty to try to help repair it,"},{"time":796840,"text":"and that's our duty now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801520,"text":"Do you remember\nat the beginning of the talk,"},{"time":803680,"text":"I said I wanted to explain\nthat the refugee crisis"},{"time":806200,"text":"was manageable, not insoluble?"},{"time":809040,"text":"That's true. I want you\nto think in a new way,"},{"time":811680,"text":"but I also want you to do things."},{"time":815680,"text":"If you're an employer,"},{"time":817880,"text":"hire refugees."},{"time":820440,"text":"If you're persuaded by the arguments,"},{"time":823280,"text":"take on the myths"},{"time":824800,"text":"when family or friends\nor workmates repeat them."},{"time":828440,"text":"If you've got money, give it to charities"},{"time":830720,"text":"that make a difference\nfor refugees around the world."},{"time":833520,"text":"If you're a citizen,"},{"time":836040,"text":"vote for politicians"},{"time":838400,"text":"who will put into practice\nthe solutions that I've talked about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842040,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":846280,"text":"The duty to strangers"},{"time":848480,"text":"shows itself"},{"time":850480,"text":"in small ways and big,"},{"time":853040,"text":"prosaic and heroic."},{"time":855800,"text":"In 1942,"},{"time":858600,"text":"my aunt and my grandmother\nwere living in Brussels"},{"time":861000,"text":"under German occupation."},{"time":864000,"text":"They received a summons"},{"time":866360,"text":"from the Nazi authorities\nto go to Brussels Railway Station."},{"time":872280,"text":"My grandmother immediately thought\nsomething was amiss."},{"time":876720,"text":"She pleaded with her relatives"},{"time":879240,"text":"not to go to Brussels Railway Station."},{"time":882240,"text":"Her relatives said to her,"},{"time":885440,"text":"\"If we don't go,\nif we don't do what we're told,"},{"time":888240,"text":"then we're going to be in trouble.\""},{"time":890760,"text":"You can guess what happened"},{"time":892720,"text":"to the relatives who went\nto Brussels Railway Station."},{"time":896160,"text":"They were never seen again."},{"time":898160,"text":"But my grandmother and my aunt,"},{"time":900720,"text":"they went to a small village"},{"time":903280,"text":"south of Brussels"},{"time":905720,"text":"where they'd been on holiday\nin the decade before,"},{"time":909280,"text":"and they presented themselves\nat the house of the local farmer,"},{"time":912960,"text":"a Catholic farmer called Monsieur Maurice,"},{"time":915840,"text":"and they asked him to take them in."},{"time":918880,"text":"And he did,"},{"time":920560,"text":"and by the end of the war,"},{"time":922920,"text":"17 Jews, I was told,\nwere living in that village."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928360,"text":"And when I was teenager, I asked my aunt,"},{"time":930360,"text":"\"Can you take me to meet\nMonsieur Maurice?\""},{"time":933400,"text":"And she said, \"Yeah, I can.\nHe's still alive. Let's go and see him.\""},{"time":936640,"text":"And so, it must have been '83, '84,"},{"time":939320,"text":"we went to see him."},{"time":940720,"text":"And I suppose, like only a teenager could,"},{"time":943560,"text":"when I met him,"},{"time":944840,"text":"he was this white-haired gentleman,"},{"time":948320,"text":"I said to him,"},{"time":951160,"text":"\"Why did you do it?"},{"time":953400,"text":"Why did you take that risk?\""},{"time":957240,"text":"And he looked at me and he shrugged,"},{"time":959000,"text":"and he said, in French,"},{"time":961240,"text":"\"On doit.\""},{"time":962600,"text":"\"One must.\""},{"time":964280,"text":"It was innate in him."},{"time":967120,"text":"It was natural."},{"time":968400,"text":"And my point to you is it should be\nnatural and innate in us, too."},{"time":972640,"text":"Tell yourself,"},{"time":975080,"text":"this refugee crisis is manageable,"},{"time":977600,"text":"not unsolvable,"},{"time":979200,"text":"and each one of us"},{"time":981320,"text":"has a personal responsibility\nto help make it so."},{"time":985240,"text":"Because this is about the rescue\nof us and our values"},{"time":989440,"text":"as well as the rescue\nof refugees and their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992320,"text":"Thank you very much indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":993640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005120,"text":"Bruno Giussani: David, thank you.\nDavid Miliband: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008000,"text":"BG: Those are strong suggestions"},{"time":1009600,"text":"and your call for individual\nresponsibility is very strong as well,"},{"time":1012800,"text":"but I'm troubled\nby one thought, and it's this:"},{"time":1015040,"text":"you mentioned, and these are your words,\n\"extraordinary Western leadership\""},{"time":1019080,"text":"which led 60-something years ago"},{"time":1020960,"text":"to the whole discussion\nabout human rights,"},{"time":1023040,"text":"to the conventions on refugees, etc. etc."},{"time":1027240,"text":"That leadership\nhappened after a big trauma"},{"time":1029640,"text":"and happened in\na consensual political space,"},{"time":1033640,"text":"and now we are\nin a divisive political space."},{"time":1035800,"text":"Actually, refugees have become\none of the divisive issues."},{"time":1038560,"text":"So where will leadership come from today?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041160,"text":"DM: Well, I think that you're right to say"},{"time":1043640,"text":"that the leadership forged in war"},{"time":1046760,"text":"has a different temper\nand a different tempo"},{"time":1049040,"text":"and a different outlook"},{"time":1050320,"text":"than leadership forged in peace."},{"time":1053560,"text":"And so my answer would be\nthe leadership has got to come from below,"},{"time":1057320,"text":"not from above."},{"time":1058800,"text":"I mean, a recurring theme\nof the conference this week"},{"time":1062160,"text":"has been about\nthe democratization of power."},{"time":1066000,"text":"And we've got to preserve\nour own democracies,"},{"time":1068200,"text":"but we've got to also activate\nour own democracies."},{"time":1070720,"text":"And when people say to me,"},{"time":1072560,"text":"\"There's a backlash against refugees,\""},{"time":1074440,"text":"what I say to them is,"},{"time":1075720,"text":"\"No, there's a polarization,"},{"time":1077840,"text":"and at the moment,"},{"time":1079080,"text":"those who are fearful\nare making more noise"},{"time":1081104,"text":"than those who are proud.\""},{"time":1082640,"text":"And so my answer to your question\nis that we will sponsor and encourage"},{"time":1086640,"text":"and give confidence to leadership"},{"time":1088440,"text":"when we mobilize ourselves."},{"time":1090240,"text":"And I think that when you are\nin a position of looking for leadership,"},{"time":1093560,"text":"you have to look inside"},{"time":1094920,"text":"and mobilize in your own community"},{"time":1096640,"text":"to try to create conditions\nfor a different kind of settlement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1099880,"text":"BG: Thank you, David.\nThanks for coming to TED."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1102120,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}